  "soap_summary": "Patient presenting with an acute left-sided, throbbing headache today with preceding visual aura (zigzag lines), blurred vision, photophobia, nausea and vomiting x2. Headache is worsened by movement/neck movement. Denies fever or rash. Has had a similar headache a few weeks ago and is on Microgynon (combined OCP) for 3 months. Physician suspects a migraine-type headache (unconfirmed). Advised symptomatic treatment (paracetamol, co-codamol, NSAIDs), headache diary, and to return if symptoms worsen or new focal deficits develop.",
